  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations:\n\n1. United States Approach\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Comprehensive federal regulations\n- Strong emphasis on reporting suspicious transactions\n- Significant criminal and civil penalties\n- Robust asset forfeiture mechanisms\n\n2. European Union Approach\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directive (AMLD)\n- Supranational regulatory framework\n- Harmonized regulations across member states\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n- Focus on transparency and beneficial ownership\n\n3. United Kingdom Approach\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Strict regulatory compliance\n- Advanced financial intelligence mechanisms\n- Strong international cooperation\n- Comprehensive risk-based assessment framework\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Traditional banking secrecy laws\n- Increasingly transparent regulatory environment\n- Enhanced international cooperation\n- Sophisticated financial monitoring systems\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Strict capital controls\n- Growing emphasis on international compliance\n- Developing comprehensive legal framework\n\n6. Canada\n- Proceeds of Crime (Money Laundering) Act\n- Risk-based compliance model\n- Strong international collaboration\n- Comprehensive reporting requirements\n\nCommon Elements:\n- Financial institution reporting obligations\n- Customer identification protocols\n- Suspicious transaction monitoring\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\nVariations emerge in enforcement intensity, regulatory complexity, and specific implementation strategies.",
